wanna hear an interesting story about Japan that is very random?
ok - so there was this park where they charged admission- it was like 200 yen- about 2 dollars to enter per person

well they had an older man on duty to take the money from people entering - however- this person was scared by all the foreign people that for nearly 10 years he didnt take any money from any foreigners
they estimated that he lost the park over a hundred thousand dollars a year because of this
Not even wanting to take mone
they said he experience paralyzing fear of being unable to understand or explain to people who didnt speak Japanese
yet he kept that job for over 10 years!
So less xenophobia and more just typical social anxiety but cranked up, lol
his fear was the communication breakdown
he wasnt confidant in his ability to speak english much less any other language - even though he did have training in it
can you imagine doing that for that long?
